# ProjectFlo — Brand Scoping

- Canonical transport header is **`X-Brand-Context`**. Never introduce `X-Brand-Id` or other variants.
- `brandId` query params are legacy compatibility only; do not add them to new endpoints or new client code.

## Frontend
- Brand context comes from the canonical `@/features/platform/brand` API (provider/hook).
- Shared API client injects `X-Brand-Context` automatically; React Query keys must include brand context so cache invalidates on brand switch.

## Backend
- Controllers must resolve brand ID consistently using the shared pattern (no per-controller reimplementations).
- Services must apply brand filters on all tenant-scoped queries; list endpoints should fail fast when brand scope is missing unless explicitly documented.

## Pre-merge checklist
- No new `brandId` query params.
- Header name is exactly `X-Brand-Context`.
- Backend service queries include brand filters.
- React Query cache keys/invalidation are brand-scoped.

